&lt;h3 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Executive - Air Force Background&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Type of work: Onsite - Washington DC, 20-30% travel required&lt;br&gt;OTE: $190,000–$210,000&lt;br&gt;50% base / 50% commission&lt;br&gt;Equity included&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Client&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our client is a defense-focused technology company that provides data, analytics, and software solutions to help government leaders make faster, better-informed decisions. Their platform supports the U.S. Department of Defense and federal agencies across areas such as logistics, supply chain, readiness, and resource allocation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and execute early-stage sales activities across DoD and Fed Civ accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prospect effectively through outbound outreach (cold calling, email, conferences)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver clear, compelling value propositions and customer pitches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct discovery calls and support business development meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop written and verbal business cases, summaries, and customer readouts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with senior sales leaders in a team-selling model&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support pipeline progression across live opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn and apply a structured sales methodology through a formal onboarding and training program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must-Haves&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Military officer background strongly preferred (O-3 / O-4 ideal, but open to enlisted with logistics expertise)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Background in Air Force&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep familiarity with a DoD service branch or Federal Civilian environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort engaging senior military and civilian leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills (written and verbal)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coachable, intellectually curious, and highly motivated&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to learn sales from the ground up in a performance-driven environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice-to-Haves&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Subject matter expertise in logistics, supply chain, sustainment, or operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior exposure to defense tech, analytics, or enterprise software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

