&lt;h3 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Colorado Springs, CO. On-site at the general aviation airport.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Co-Founder (based in Colorado)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;$125K base + up to 40% performance-based bonus (linearly scaled off operating profit; uncapped upside above target). On-target total comp ~$200K. Equity available in the right circumstances.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start date:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Immediate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Client&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The company is a veteran-owned general aviation maintenance business. It launched in 2025 with a greenfield hangar in Southern California and made its first acquisition in early 2026, taking over a well-established GA maintenance shop in Colorado Springs with a long local operating history. The company has an active acquisition pipeline and expects to add at least one additional location by the end of 2026. The core business is piston and turboprop aircraft maintenance, repair, and upgrades. The Colorado Springs location has a unique special-mission systems integration capability, installing advanced sensor payloads and integrating holistic aircraft systems in platforms ranging from small turboprops through light and medium jets. The company also operates a special-operations aircraft fleet composed of piston and turboprop aircraft, doing contracted work for both government and civilian entities. They are bootstrapped, growing fast, and building a business they intend to operate for a long time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Colorado Springs shop the company acquired brings a strong local reputation and a real customer base to work with. The task is to take full P&amp;amp;L ownership of the location, grow it materially through both civilian GA and government/subcontracting special-mission integration work, and become the operator around whom the rest of the roll-up is built. This is a Location GM seat with a clear path to Regional and Corporate leadership as the business scales. They are actively pursuing additional acquisitions, and the right person here will be positioned to take on more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P&amp;amp;L&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full accountability for revenue, gross margin, and operating profit at the Colorado Springs location&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Weekly and monthly financial management: cash, receivables, working capital, vendor terms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pricing discipline across GA maintenance, avionics upgrades, and government subcontract work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Day-to-day management of the shop: technicians, avionics engineers, scheduling, quality control, and customer intake&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;FAA compliance and accountable-manager-adjacent program administration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safety and airworthiness culture; the standard for how the shop works on customer aircraft&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer service: being the face of the business to drive reputation, retention, and growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
